NASA's P-3B aircraft flies over a melange of floating ice where two glaciers meet, in eastern Greenland, on Apr. 14.  Operation IceBridge  conducts flights over Greenland, the Arctic and Antarctic, measuring surface elevation and thickness of ice sheets, and snow depth. Visit  www.bloomberg.com/sustainability  for the latest from Bloomberg News about energy, natural resources and global business.